titles, from works by Lewis Carroll to Mark Twain; from "A Tale of Two
Cities" to "Son of Tarzan".  Look in the `/etext/etext92' and
`/etext/etext93' directories.  6 p.m. - 9 a.m.

   `nptn.org' In the `pub/e.texts/gutenberg/etext91' and `etext92'
directories, you can get copies of Aesop's Fables, works by Lewis
Carroll and other works of literature, as well as the Book of Mormon.
Available 24 hours.

   `world.std.com' The `obi' directory has everything from online fables
to accounts of Hiroshima survivors.  6 p.m. - 6 a.m.


